    <div class="seo-content">
      <h2>Why Use an eSIM for International Travel?</h2>
      <p>Gone are the days of hunting down a local kiosk at the airport, fumbling with tiny physical SIM cards, and accidentally losing your home number. An eSIM (embedded SIM) allows you to download a digital data plan directly to your compatible smartphone before you even board your flight.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Instant Connectivity:</strong> Connect to local networks the moment you land.</li>
        <li><strong>Keep Your Home Number:</strong> Run dual SIMs to keep your primary number active for SMS (like banking 2FA) while using the eSIM for cheap data.</li>
        <li><strong>Cost-Effective:</strong> Avoid exorbitant roaming charges from your home carrier (which can often be $10+ per day).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Choosing the Right Provider: Fixed vs. Unlimited Data</h2>
      <p>When selecting between providers like <strong>Airalo</strong> and <strong>Holafly</strong>, the biggest decision is whether you need fixed data or unlimited data.</p>
      <p>If you rely on Wi-Fi at your accommodation or coworking space and only need data for maps, messaging, and light browsing, a fixed-data plan (e.g., 3GB or 5GB from Airalo) is usually the most cost-effective option. However, if you plan on streaming, heavily using social media, or navigating constantly without Wi-Fi, an unlimited plan (like Holafly) provides peace of mind, though you should verify their hotspot policies if you plan to tether to your laptop.</p>

      <h2>Regional vs. Local Plans</h2>
      <p>If your trip involves crossing multiple borders (like a Eurotrip or a tour of Southeast Asia), buying a <strong>Regional eSIM</strong> is highly recommended. Providers like <strong>Ubigi</strong> and <strong>Airalo</strong> offer excellent regional packages (e.g., "Eurolink" or "Asialink") that automatically switch to the best local networks as you cross borders, saving you the hassle of buying a new eSIM for every country.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <script is:inline>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const searchInput = document.getElementById('search-input');
      const filterBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.filter-btn');
      const sortSelect = document.getElementById('sort-select');
      const grid = document.getElementById('cards-grid');
      const cards = Array.from(grid.querySelectorAll('.esim-item'));
      const noResults = document.getElementById('no-results');

      let currentFilter = 'all';

      // Filtering Logic
      function applyFilters() {
        const query = searchInput.value.toLowerCase().trim();
        let visibleCount = 0;

        cards.forEach(card => {
          const textContent = card.innerText.toLowerCase();
          const isUnlimited = card.getAttribute('data-unlimited') === 'true';
          const isRegional = card.getAttribute('data-regional') === 'true';

          let matchesSearch = textContent.includes(query);
          let matchesFilter = true;

          if (currentFilter === 'unlimited') {
            matchesFilter = isUnlimited;
          } else if (currentFilter === 'regional') {
            matchesFilter = isRegional;
          }

          if (matchesSearch && matchesFilter) {
            card.classList.remove('hidden');
            visibleCount++;
          } else {
            card.classList.add('hidden');
          }
        });

        if (visibleCount === 0) {
          noResults.style.display = 'block';
        } else {
          noResults.style.display = 'none';
        }
      }

      // Sorting Logic
      function applySort() {
        const sortValue = sortSelect.value;

        cards.sort((a, b) => {
          const scoreA = parseFloat(a.getAttribute('data-score'));
          const scoreB = parseFloat(b.getAttribute('data-score'));
          const nameA = a.getAttribute('data-name');
          const nameB = b.getAttribute('data-name');

          if (sortValue === 'score-desc') return scoreB - scoreA;
          if (sortValue === 'name-asc') return nameA.localeCompare(nameB);
          return 0;
        });

        // Append in new order
        cards.forEach(card => grid.insertBefore(card, noResults));
      }

      // Event Listeners
      searchInput.addEventListener('input', applyFilters);

      filterBtns.forEach(btn => {
        btn.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
          filterBtns.forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
          e.target.classList.add('active');
          currentFilter = e.target.getAttribute('data-filter');
          applyFilters();
        });
      });

      sortSelect.addEventListener('change', applySort);

      // Initial Sort
      applySort();
    });
  </script>

  <!-- Pillar Guide Link -->
